stylometry:
When determining how much inventory to order one must consider if their company wants to run out of product or not. Many companies put values on what happens if they do not have enough product. If this is not important for your company than you do not have to worry so much about when to reorder. You must decide when to reorder and how much to reorder. 

EOQ is economic order quantity. EOQ is the number to order that will fulfill the economic want, or demand of a certain product. It minimizes the holding cost of inventory and the ordering costs of a product. 

TC= PC+OC+HC

TC: Total Cost
PC: Purchasing Cost
OC: Ordering Cost 
HC: Holding Cost
